column5: Got a real nice beauty this morning on Cooks, 37 inches had to be around 15 pounds!
What did ya get it on.
Nice!!!!  What a perfect specimen. Look at the colour on that fish!
Meeps Giant Killer
Nice esox
Beauty pike!
Nice esox  Ya just had to go and use that fancy word didnt ya.................  Nice pike.
We tried today,A two pound smallie,couple one pounders.Saw a big one swim by.Nice Pike .Great colors !!!!
That is a goody, why yes it is!
nice fish
Nice gator bud!
Thanks guys!
Right on man!  Is that your biggest on Cooks?
Nope, the one in my profile picture is my biggest on cooks, 41 inches... I've had a couple 37s, 36s, 35s, most of the ones I catch are in the 28-34 inch range
Yup, that Mepps sure was a Giant  Killer.  Congatulations LefroyFrisherman.  That's a real beauty you caught.
Wow, beauty pike!!
Nice fish man, congrats.  Love it when its calm like that on Simcoe.  Jim
that must be the same pike that scared all the perch away when I went ice fishing   .  JK nice fish!
I actually hate fishing for pike on Simcoe when it's calm, I like to drift and cover lots of water and cast
Couldnt agree more, i hate calm days on simcoe unless im going out with my wife and baby. Give me a mean chop that will keep a few boats at home and let me ride the waves to fish!
Nice catch!
